cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with language models and style transfer, which are both topics within the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method that incorporates multi-task and adversarial objectives, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to non-parallel corpora, which involves text and image processing, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses a disentangled latent representation learning method, which is a technique used in neural networks, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
